.TH "lpfc_reg_vfi" 9 "lpfc_reg_vfi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_reg_vfi \- Initialize the REG_VFI mailbox command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_reg_vfi
.BI "(struct lpfcMboxq *mbox "  ","
.BI "struct lpfc_vport *vport "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t phys "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mbox" 12
pointer to lpfc mbox command to initialize.
.IP "vport" 12
vport associated with the VF.
.IP "phys" 12
BDE DMA bus address used to send the service parameters to the HBA.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine initializes \fImbox\fP to all zeros and then fills in the mailbox
fields from \fIvport\fP, and uses \fIbuf\fP as a DMAable buffer to send the vport's
fc service parameters to the HBA for this VFI. REG_VFI configures virtual
fabrics identified by VFI in the context of an FCF.
